<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12081a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12081a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12081a"> 81(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> A &mdash; We sent / M &mdash; Then we placed</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Nous leur conduis&icirc;mes Arthur. Morgan nous re&ccedil;ut avec honneur; elle fit d&eacute;poser le roi dans sa propre chambre, <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Enfin elle lui dit qu&apos;elle pourrait le gu&eacute;rir, s&apos;il restait pr&egrave;s d&apos;elle tant que cela serait n&eacute;cessaire, et s&apos;il voulait se soumettre &agrave; ses soins. &ldquo;Heureux de cette bonne nouvelle, nous lui avons confi&eacute; le roi, et nous avons remis &agrave; la voile. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[<mark>We sent them Arthur</mark>. Morgan received us with honour; she put the king in her own room, [&hellip;]</font> Finally she told him that she would be able to cure him, if he stayed with her for as long as necessary, and if he submitted to her care. &lsquo;Happy with this good news, <mark>we committed the king to her care</mark>, and set sail again.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>&rsquo;] <small> [TLMM]Th&eacute;odore-Claude Hersart, Vicomte de La Villemarqu&eacute;, <cite a>Myrdhinn, ou l'enchanteur Merlin</cite></a> (1862) 133</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
